race.comment: HYDE PARK (3) has threatened his last two at Townsville, and his effort in Open grade two back over this distance reads the best. Races here for the first time and Huxtable is a positive jockey engagement. Rates well. DARLING CLEMENTINE (6) has put together two wins at the track, the latest over 1500m when she got home by 2.2L. This is a bit tougher, but she keeps improving and this is within her scope. JOURNALISM (1) finished third last start over 1460m at Home Hill, beaten 1.5L. Goes up a rung or two, but he has a handy 2kg claim and is capable of running into placings. CITIROC (7) proved too strong two runs ago but couldn't follow that up last time. He's capable of filling a minor slot.
